oc:kn_06281b1e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing optimization experiments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not end A/B tests early or test multiple variables simultaneously; calculate required sample size before starting and run for at least one full business cycle." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature test termination and confounded variables produce unreliable results that lead to wrong optimization decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_21665d5e a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing trend analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Chart metrics over at least 8-12 data points for meaningful trends; identify direction, rate of change, inflection points, seasonality, and leading indicators." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Too few data points produce noise masquerading as signal; 8-12 points minimum separates real trends from random variation" .

oc:kn_46466bcb a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting an attribution model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use position-based (U-shaped) attribution as a reasonable middle ground for most B2B companies; start with last-touch if no model is in place." ;
    oc:hasRationale "U-shaped attribution balances discovery and conversion credit without requiring the high data volume needed for data-driven models" .

oc:kn_7e65f672 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating optimization recommendations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify underperforming metrics vs target/benchmark → 2. Diagnose funnel stage (impressions, clicks, conversions, retention) → 3. Hypothesize root cause (audience, message, creative, offer, timing, technical) → 4. Prioritize by impact vs effort → 5. Test hypothesis experimentally → 6. Measure results → 7. Scale wins or iterate" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured optimization prevents ad-hoc fixes and ensures recommendations are data-linked, testable, and prioritized" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_98aa054f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing trend forecasting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Forecasts based on fewer than 12 data points should be flagged as low confidence; always present forecasts as ranges, not exact numbers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Low data point counts produce unreliable trend lines that can mislead stakeholders into false precision" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d8d94f1a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting the Key Metrics Dashboard" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use consistent status indicators across all metrics: On track (meeting/exceeding target), At risk (below target but acceptable), Off track (significantly below target). Use green/yellow/red color coding." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent visual language enables rapid scanning and prioritization by stakeholders" .

oc:kn_dd630f00 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing the metrics dashboard section of any report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with metrics that map to business objectives (not vanity metrics); show trends over time, not point-in-time snapshots; keep dashboards to one page with detail in appendix." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Executive stakeholders need trend context and business-aligned metrics to make decisions; point-in-time snapshots lack actionable context" .

oc:kn_f601be20 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When interpreting attribution data and making channel optimization decisions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not optimize one channel in isolation based on single-touch attribution; awareness channels always look bad in last-touch models and conversion channels look bad in first-touch models." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-touch attribution creates systematic bias that leads to misallocated budget and poor strategic decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

